<figureCitation box="[260,274,1787,1811]" captionStart="FIGURE 8" captionStartId="16.[151,250,1193,1215]" captionTargetBox="[178,1407,208,1145]" captionTargetId="figure@16.[150,1436,193,1172]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="FIGURE 8. Stegana (Steganina) spatulata sp. nov., male terminalia: A. Epandrium, surstylus and cercus (lateral view); B. Surstylus (inner view); C, D. Hypandrium, parameres, aedeagus and aedeagal apodeme (ventral and lateral views); E, F. Gonopods (ventral and lateral views); G. Tenth sternite (ventral view). Scale lines = 0.1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2624702/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="95">8</figureCitation>
