<subSubSection pageId="14" pageNumber="95" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="14.[151,1436,1858,2027]" pageId="14" pageNumber="95">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,273,1858,1883]" pageId="14" pageNumber="95">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
This species resembles 
<taxonomicName authority="Strobl, 1898" authorityName="Strobl" authorityYear="1898" box="[553,860,1858,1883]" class="Insecta" family="Drosophilidae" genus="Stegana" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="95" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nigrithorax">
<emphasis box="[553,710,1859,1883]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="95">S. nigrithorax</emphasis>
Strobl, 
<quantity box="[804,860,1859,1883]" metricMagnitude="1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.820919999999999" pageId="14" pageNumber="95" unit="in" value="1898.0">1898</quantity>
</taxonomicName>
in some characters of the colour patterns of body (
<figureCitation box="[159,244,1894,1919]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="10.[151,250,1909,1931]" captionTargetBox="[255,1340,253,1893]" captionTargetId="figure@10.[251,1340,193,1894]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURE 2. Habitus. A. Stegana (Steganina) toyaensis Okada &amp; Sidorenko, 1992; B–J in holotype: B. Stegana (Steganina) latitabula sp. nov.; C. Stegana (Steganina) panda sp. nov.; D. Stegana (Steganina) pinguifoliacea sp. nov.; E. Stegana (Steganina) spatulata, sp. nov.; F. Stegana (Steganina) stachydifolia, sp. nov.; G. Stegana (Steganina) hirtifoliacea sp. nov.; H. Stegana (Steganina) unguiculata sp. nov.; I. Stegana (Steganina) biflava sp. nov.; J. Stegana (Steganina) flavivittata sp. nov." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2624690/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="95">Fig. 2E</figureCitation>
) and semicircular gonopods (
<figureCitation box="[577,663,1894,1919]" captionStart="FIGURE 8" captionStartId="16.[151,250,1193,1215]" captionTargetBox="[178,1407,208,1145]" captionTargetId="figure@16.[150,1436,193,1172]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="FIGURE 8. Stegana (Steganina) spatulata sp. nov., male terminalia: A. Epandrium, surstylus and cercus (lateral view); B. Surstylus (inner view); C, D. Hypandrium, parameres, aedeagus and aedeagal apodeme (ventral and lateral views); E, F. Gonopods (ventral and lateral views); G. Tenth sternite (ventral view). Scale lines = 0.1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2624702/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="95">Fig. 8E</figureCitation>
), but can be distinguished by the median flaps of hypandrium (
<bibRefCitation author="Hu, Y. G. &amp; Toda, M. J." pageId="14" pageNumber="95" pagination="151 - 160" refId="ref10331" refString="Hu, Y. G. &amp; Toda, M. J. (1994) The Stegana (Steganina) coleoptrata species-group (Diptera, Drosophilidae), with descriptions of two new species and new records from eastern Palearctic region. Japanese Journal of Entomology, 62, 151 - 160." type="journal article" year="1994">Hu &amp; Toda, 1994</bibRefCitation>
; fused gonopod in 
<bibRefCitation author="Bachli, G. &amp; Vilela, C. R. &amp; Escher, S. A. &amp; Saura, A." box="[512,731,1930,1955]" pageId="14" pageNumber="95" pagination="362" refId="ref9789" refString="Bachli, G., Vilela, C. R., Escher, S. A. &amp; Saura, A. (2004) The Drosophilidae (Diptera) of Fennoscandia and Denmark. In: Fauna Entomologica Scandinavica. Fol. 39. Brill, Leiden, New York, pp. 362." type="book chapter" year="2004">
Bächli 
<emphasis box="[596,648,1931,1955]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="95">et al</emphasis>
., 2004
</bibRefCitation>
) concave, spoon-like (
<figureCitation box="[996,1120,1930,1955]" captionStart="FIGURE 8" captionStartId="16.[151,250,1193,1215]" captionTargetBox="[178,1407,208,1145]" captionTargetId="figure@16.[150,1436,193,1172]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="FIGURE 8. Stegana (Steganina) spatulata sp. nov., male terminalia: A. Epandrium, surstylus and cercus (lateral view); B. Surstylus (inner view); C, D. Hypandrium, parameres, aedeagus and aedeagal apodeme (ventral and lateral views); E, F. Gonopods (ventral and lateral views); G. Tenth sternite (ventral view). Scale lines = 0.1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2624702/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="95">Fig. 8E, F</figureCitation>
); aedeagus with numerous, serrated, minute processes medially (
<figureCitation box="[568,693,1966,1991]" captionStart="FIGURE 8" captionStartId="16.[151,250,1193,1215]" captionTargetBox="[178,1407,208,1145]" captionTargetId="figure@16.[150,1436,193,1172]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="FIGURE 8. Stegana (Steganina) spatulata sp. nov., male terminalia: A. Epandrium, surstylus and cercus (lateral view); B. Surstylus (inner view); C, D. Hypandrium, parameres, aedeagus and aedeagal apodeme (ventral and lateral views); E, F. Gonopods (ventral and lateral views); G. Tenth sternite (ventral view). Scale lines = 0.1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2624702/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="95">Fig. 8C, D</figureCitation>
). However, the minimum interspecific genetic distance is 3.1% to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Chen &amp; Chen" authorityYear="2008" box="[151,291,2003,2027]" class="Insecta" family="Drosophilidae" genus="Stegana" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="95" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pililobosa">
<emphasis box="[151,291,2003,2027]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="95">S. pililobosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<tableCitation box="[305,393,2002,2027]" captionStart="TABLE 2" captionStartId="23.[147,225,546,566]" captionText="TABLE 2. Genetic distances within and between the 130 mtCOI sequences of 38 species of the coleoptrata, ornatipes, and undulata groups involved in the molecular analysis." pageId="14" pageNumber="95">Table 2</tableCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="15" pageNumber="96" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="15.[151,1436,151,645]" pageId="15" pageNumber="96">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,345,151,176]" pageId="15" pageNumber="96">Description.</emphasis>
Male: Frons brown. First flagellomere yellow on basal 1/4, brown on distal 3/4. Clypeus yellow, slightly brownish medially. Palpus yellow. Katepisternum entirely white. Scutellum brown (
<figureCitation box="[1216,1307,188,213]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="10.[151,250,1909,1931]" captionTargetBox="[255,1340,253,1893]" captionTargetId="figure@10.[251,1340,193,1894]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURE 2. Habitus. A. Stegana (Steganina) toyaensis Okada &amp; Sidorenko, 1992; B–J in holotype: B. Stegana (Steganina) latitabula sp. nov.; C. Stegana (Steganina) panda sp. nov.; D. Stegana (Steganina) pinguifoliacea sp. nov.; E. Stegana (Steganina) spatulata, sp. nov.; F. Stegana (Steganina) stachydifolia, sp. nov.; G. Stegana (Steganina) hirtifoliacea sp. nov.; H. Stegana (Steganina) unguiculata sp. nov.; I. Stegana (Steganina) biflava sp. nov.; J. Stegana (Steganina) flavivittata sp. nov." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2624690/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="96">Fig. 2E</figureCitation>
). Femur of foreleg with 5 long erect setae near distal part of posteroventral surface. Abdominal tergites entirely dark brown medially, yellowish brown laterally (
<figureCitation box="[563,650,260,285]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="10.[151,250,1909,1931]" captionTargetBox="[255,1340,253,1893]" captionTargetId="figure@10.[251,1340,193,1894]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURE 2. Habitus. A. Stegana (Steganina) toyaensis Okada &amp; Sidorenko, 1992; B–J in holotype: B. Stegana (Steganina) latitabula sp. nov.; C. Stegana (Steganina) panda sp. nov.; D. Stegana (Steganina) pinguifoliacea sp. nov.; E. Stegana (Steganina) spatulata, sp. nov.; F. Stegana (Steganina) stachydifolia, sp. nov.; G. Stegana (Steganina) hirtifoliacea sp. nov.; H. Stegana (Steganina) unguiculata sp. nov.; I. Stegana (Steganina) biflava sp. nov.; J. Stegana (Steganina) flavivittata sp. nov." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2624690/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="96">Fig. 2E</figureCitation>
). Male terminalia (
<figureCitation box="[863,931,260,285]" captionStart="FIGURE 8" captionStartId="16.[151,250,1193,1215]" captionTargetBox="[178,1407,208,1145]" captionTargetId="figure@16.[150,1436,193,1172]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="FIGURE 8. Stegana (Steganina) spatulata sp. nov., male terminalia: A. Epandrium, surstylus and cercus (lateral view); B. Surstylus (inner view); C, D. Hypandrium, parameres, aedeagus and aedeagal apodeme (ventral and lateral views); E, F. Gonopods (ventral and lateral views); G. Tenth sternite (ventral view). Scale lines = 0.1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2624702/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="96">Fig. 8</figureCitation>
): Epandrium protruded ventrally, with ca. 20 setae on posterior portion per side. Surstylus distally with numerous setulae on inner surface. Cercus lacking pubescence. Tenth sternite with 1 pair of processes submedially. Paramere lacking setula.
</paragraph>
